Sports News, Opinion, Scores, Schedules
The Barkley Marathons is a 100 mile race that is known as the toughest race in the world. In it's 32 year history, only 15 people have managed to finish. Canadian Ultrarunner Gary Robbins made his first attempt in 2016 and was unsuccessful. He would return in 2017 only to suffer a crushing defeat that gained worldwide attention. In 2017/2018 TSN followed Gary and his family on their journey back to the Barkley in the pursuit to become just the 16th person and the first Canadian to ever finish. Here is a preview.